name: Goldeneye (Cart Only)
description: The pinnacle of the FPS genre on the N64. One of the games that everyone HAS to own. Cart only, near mint condition.

name: Turok 2 (Cart Only)
description: Turok returns in a truly amazing new adventure, delving deep into the core of a violently twisted world in order to find and destroy the Primagen. Featuring a world of gruesome enemies, explosive new weaponry and a multi-player death match that will leave you breathless… This game received a score of 94% back in the November 98 issue of the official Nintendo mag, and apparently its the scariest game ever on the N64. Cart only, near mint condition.

name: Turok Rage Wars (Boxed)
description: Boxed copy of the third installment in the Turok franchise. Up to 4 player brutal FPS combat over 36 multi player levels, with 16 different weapons and 12 different power ups. Sweet. Box slightly tatty, but cartridge and manual are near mint.

name: Official Controller (Loose)
description: Voted the best video games console controller ever. The original and official N64 controller, tested and working with no loose stick! Supplied unboxed in very good condition. Check the circle to choose the colour you want.

name: N64 Console and 1 Official Controller (Loose)
description: The last mainstream console to ever use a cartridge based storage system and something everyone should own! Code named project reality in 1993 and announced under the name the Ultra 64 in 1994. The unveiling of the console was meant to come in early 1995, but was delayed until the November Shoshinkai, Nintendo’s exhibition, in Japan. The console was finally released in September 1996 and managed to sell all its initial stock. It was finally pulled from production and replaced by the disk based Gamecube in 2001, but by then had sold over 30 million units world wide, coming second only to the Sony Playstation. Tech Specs: CPU: 64-bit R4300i RISC (93.75MHz) / 64-bit data paths, registers with 5-stage pipelining Co-processor: 64-bit RISC (62.5MHz) RAM: 4MB (36Mb) upgradeable Graphics: Pixel Drawing Processor (RDP) built into co-processor Colors: 16.7 million (32,000 on screen) Polygons: 150,000 per second Resolution: 640×480 pixels Sound: 16 to 24-channel 16-bit stereo (up to 100 PCM channels possible) Supplied loose with one official controller, official power supply unit and official RF unit. Refurbished condition.
